GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 2
SENATE BILL 108
Education/Higher Education Committee Substitute Adopted 4/30/25
Short Title: Johnston County/Johnston CC Construction. (Local)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
February 18, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT PROVIDING THAT JOHNSTON COUNTY IS AUTHORIZED TO CONSTRUCT
3 COMMUNITY COLLEGE BUILDINGS ON THE CAMPUSES OF JOHNSTON
4 COMMUNITY COLLEGE.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1.(a) Notwithstanding G.S. 115D-9, 115D-15.1, and 143-341(3) or any
7 other provision of law, Johnston County (hereinafter "County") is hereby authorized to construct
8 community college buildings, as that term is defined in G.S. 143-336, on the campuses of
9 Johnston Community College (hereinafter "College"). For the purposes of this act, the terms
10 "construct" and "construction" include making additions, improvements, renovations, or repairs
11 to all or any part of a community college building. The County may finance the construction of
12 these buildings in accordance with Article 8 of Chapter 159 of the General Statutes and
13 G.S. 160A-20. If the County finances the construction of any building on the College's campuses,
14 the College Board of Trustees may, in connection with the construction, transfer any of its
15 property to the County to be used for security for the financing agreement. The County shall
16 transfer the property back to the College Board of Trustees when any financing agreement
17 entered into by the County to finance the construction has been satisfied. The County may also
18 construct the community college buildings using other funding sources, including appropriations
19 made by the General Assembly. Upon completion of the construction of the buildings, the County
20 shall lease the buildings to the College under the terms and conditions agreed to by both the
21 County and the College.
22 SECTION 1.(b) In constructing buildings as authorized by this act, the County does
23 not have to comply with the provisions of G.S. 115D-9 or Part 1 of Article 36 of Chapter 143 of
24 the General Statutes. However, the County shall comply with the provisions of Articles 3D and
25 8 of Chapter 143 of the General Statutes. The County shall consult with the College Board of
26 Trustees about programming requirements for the buildings and shall keep the Board informed
27 as to the construction process and progress.
28 SECTION 1.(c) Prior to the construction of any building authorized by this act, the
29 County and College Board of Trustees shall enter into a memorandum of understanding that sets
30 forth the roles and responsibilities of each party for the construction of community college
31 buildings on the campuses of the College so that construction is completed in a timely fashion
32 and cost-efficient manner.
33 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies only to
34 construction projects, including additions, improvements, renovations, and repairs, coordinated
35 by the County for College uses and purposes.
